The Turkana Council of Elders in Laikipia county have asked the national government to expedite the process of issuing ID cards to the community.In a petition filed in the National Assembly, the residents, through Turkana North MP Christopher Nakuleu, want the government to stop bias in the issuance of the ID cards.&ldquo;The Constitution prohibits all forms of direct or indirect discrimination,&rdquo; the petition says.The petitioners want Interior CS Joseph Nkaissery to revoke any order directing the &ldquo;tedious&rdquo; vetting by the offices responsible for registration of persons in the county. &ldquo;The lengthy vetting process has deprived the members of the Turkana community of their rights to choose their leaders,&rdquo; the petition says.The petition is before the Administration and National Security Committee.